Terminalia (
Fig. 7 G-I
): Tergite VI and segment VII+VIII yellowish tawny with scarce silver pruinosity. Surstyili in lateral view wider, more than 2 x the maximum cerci width; triangular shaped, slightly narrowed at the apex. Surstyli in posterior view with an expansion laterally. Apex of the hypandrium directed upwards. Middle bar longer than the total length of the granular structure of distiphallus. Apex of distiphallus curved.
